==Latin==

===Etymology===
From Latin verb '''[[cantare]]''', ''sing'', [[frequentative]] verb formed from '''[[cantus]]''', ''sung'', perfect passive participle of '''[[canere]]''', ''sing''.

===Verbal Adjective===
'''cantatus''' {{m}}, '''[[cantata]]''' {{f}}, '''[[cantatum]]''' {{n}}

# [[sung]]; having been sung

====Notes====
Perfect passive participle of '''[[cantare]]''', ''sing''.  First and second conjugation.

